Before installing clsharedir, install a lisp implementation
like clisp (http://clisp.cons.org) or cmucl (http://www.cons.org/cmucl/).

First compile the source code:

$ your-lisp
> (load "load.lisp")

or

$ clisp load.lisp
or
$ cmucl --load load.lisp
or
$ your-lisp <load-option> load.lisp


Then you can put the clsharedir directory where you want and you can launch
clsharedir with:

$ your-lisp <load-option> /the/clsharedir/directory/load.lisp [options]

Optionnaly you can create a shell or batch script to automate this process.


Have fun,


Philippe Brochard



